#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn31.23"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn31.23-112:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 31 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 31 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn31.23-112:0.2"
msgid "1. Gandhabbavagga "
msgstr "1. Fairies "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 23–112. Sāragandhādidānūpakārasuttanavutika → dānupakārā 2--10 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn31.23-112:0.3"
msgid "23–112. Sāragandhādidānūpakārasuttanavutika "
msgstr "23–112. Ninety Discourses On How Giving Helps to Become a Fragrant Heartwood Fairy "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.253, sc1
msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Seated to one side, that mendicant said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.3"
msgid "“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sāragandhe adhivatthānaṃ devānaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why someone, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in the company of the gods of fairykind who live in fragrant heartwood … "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.4"
msgid "pheggugandhe adhivatthānaṃ devānaṃ … "
msgstr "softwood … "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.5"
msgid "tacagandhe adhivatthānaṃ devānaṃ … "
msgstr "bark … "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.6"
msgid "papaṭikagandhe adhivatthānaṃ devānaṃ … "
msgstr "sprouts … "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.7"
msgid "pattagandhe adhivatthānaṃ devānaṃ … "
msgstr "leaves … "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.8"
msgid "pupphagandhe adhivatthānaṃ devānaṃ … "
msgstr "flowers … "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.9"
msgid "phalagandhe adhivatthānaṃ devānaṃ … "
msgstr "fruit … "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.10"
msgid "rasagandhe adhivatthānaṃ devānaṃ … "
msgstr "sap … "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.11"
msgid "gandhagandhe adhivatthānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti? "
msgstr "fragrant scents?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.12"
msgid "“Idha, bhikkhu, ekacco kāyena sucaritaṃ carati, vācāya sucaritaṃ carati, manasā sucaritaṃ carati. "
msgstr "“Mendicant, it’s when someone does good things by way of body, speech, and mind. "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.13"
msgid "Tassa sutaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "And they’ve heard: "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.14"
msgid "‘gandhagandhe adhivatthā devā dīghāyukā vaṇṇavanto sukhabahulā’ti. "
msgstr "‘The gods of fairykind who live in fragrant scents are long-lived, beautiful, and very happy.’ "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.15"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "They think: "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.16"
msgid "‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā gandhagandhe adhivatthānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the company of the gods of fairykind who live in fragrant scents!’ "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.17"
msgid "So annaṃ deti … pe … "
msgstr "They give food … "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.18"
msgid "pānaṃ deti … "
msgstr "drink … "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.19"
msgid "vatthaṃ deti … "
msgstr "clothing … "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.20"
msgid "yānaṃ deti … "
msgstr "a vehicle … "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.21"
msgid "mālaṃ deti … "
msgstr "a garland … "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.22"
msgid "gandhaṃ deti … "
msgstr "fragrance … "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.23"
msgid "vilepanaṃ deti … "
msgstr "makeup … "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.24"
msgid "seyyaṃ deti … "
msgstr "a bed … "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.25"
msgid "āvasathaṃ deti … "
msgstr "a house … "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.26"
msgid "padīpeyyaṃ deti. "
msgstr "a lamp. "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.27"
msgid "So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā gandhagandhe adhivatthānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the gods of fairykind who live in fragrant scents. "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.28"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā gandhagandhe adhivatthānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti. "
msgstr "This is the cause, this is the reason why someone, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in the company of the gods of fairykind who live on fragrant scents.” "

msgctxt "sn31.23-112:1.29"
msgid "Dvādasasatimaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn31.23-112:2.1"
msgid "(Evaṃ piṇḍakena ekasatañca dvādasa ca suttantā honti.) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn31.23-112:2.2"
msgid "Gandhabbavaggo paṭhamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn31.23-112:3.1"
msgid "Suddhikañca sucaritaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn31.23-112:3.2"
msgid "dātā hi apare dasa; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn31.23-112:3.3"
msgid "Dānūpakārā satadhā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn31.23-112:3.4"
msgid "gandhabbe suppakāsitāti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn31.23-112:3.5"
msgid "Gandhabbakāyasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ. "
msgstr "The Linked Discourses on fairykind are completed."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
